<item>
            <title>[CXF-5348] Exception mappers implementing ExceptionMapper through an abstract class are not mapped to the declared exception </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5348</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we consider the following exception mapper, all Throwables will be mapped instead of only the SomeClientExceptions :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Provider
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;SomeClientExceptionMapper &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; AbstractBadRequestExceptionMapper&amp;lt;SomeClientException&amp;gt; {}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;abstract&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;AbstractBadRequestExceptionMapper&amp;lt;T &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; Throwable&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;implements&lt;/span&gt; ExceptionMapper&amp;lt;T&amp;gt; {

    @Override
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; Response toResponse(T exception) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; Response.status(Status.BAD_REQUEST).entity(exception.getMessage()).build();
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please find attached, a sample project with some ITs showing the problem.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
